objects.name: Agriculture and agribusiness
objects.description: Private entities specialized in the growth, culture, transport and transformation of plants or livestock for food.

objects.name: Logistics
objects.description: Entities managing the flow of goods, equipment, materials, supplies etc.

objects.name: Culture and entertainment
objects.description: Public and private entities dealing with cultural, sport activities and entertainment.

objects.name: Culture
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in creating, producting, and distributing goods and services that are cultural in nature, or protecting it.
Sector Culture is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Sports
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in producing, organizing, promoting  goods and services associated with sports.
Sector Sports is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Entertainment industry
objects.description: All entities involved in the conception and production of entertainment products, such as music, movies or video games.
Sector Entertainment industry is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Gambling
objects.description: All companies or public organizations involved in gambling activities, such as casino, money games, etc.
Sector Gambling is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Education
objects.description: Public or private entities operating to facilitate learning and acquiring knowledge and skills, composed of infrastructures and services to host teachers, students, and administrative services related to this activity. This does not include research activities.

objects.name: Universities
objects.description: Public and private institutions for higher education.
Sector Universities is a subsector of Education

objects.name: Schools
objects.description: PPublic and private institutions for all primary and secondary school levels.
Sector Schools is a subsector of Education

objects.name: Energy
objects.description: Public and private entities operating to extract, store, transport and process fuel, entities managing energy plants and energy storage and distribution and entities managing fuel waste.

objects.name: Electricity
objects.description: Public or private entities involved in the storage, transport and distribution of electricity to end customers.
Sector Electricity is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Nuclear power (civilian use)
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the extraction and transport of nuclear fuel, operating nuclear plants for civilian purposes and entities processing nuclear waste.
Sector Nuclear power (civilian use) is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Gas
objects.description: Public or private entities involved in exploration, extraction, refining, transporting and marketing of natural gas products.
Sector Gas is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Oil
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the global processes of exploration, extraction, refining, transporting and marketing of petroleum products.
Sector Oil is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Renewable energies
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the production of electricity based on renewable ressources.
Sector Renewable energies is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Transport
objects.description: All entities involved in the movement of people or goods from one place to another.

objects.name: Air transport
objects.description: All entities transporting people or goods by plane, managing or exploiting airports and structures, traffic authorities and plane manufacturers. Includes all civilian space activities.
Sector Air transport is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Rail transport
objects.description: Public and private entities managing rail infrastructures, rail transportation, exploiting intelligent rail transport systems and the rail industry.
Sector Rail transport is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Maritime transport
objects.description: All entities transporting people or good by naval means, managing or exploiting naval structures (ports), naval constructors and traffic authorities.
Sector Maritime transport is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Road transport
objects.description: Public and private entities managing road infrastructures, road transportation, exploiting intelligent transport systems and the automotive industry.
Sector Road transport is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Defense
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the conception and production of weapons and the planning and conducting of military operations.

objects.name: Defense ministries (including the military)
objects.description: Includes the military and all defense related-space activities.
Sector Defense ministries (including the military) is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Defense industry
objects.description: All private contractors involved in the manufacturing and sale of weapons and military or defense technologies.
Sector Defense industry is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Defense research and development
objects.description: R&D for defense or military purposes.
Sector Defense research and development is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Finance
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the allocation of assets and liabilities over space and time.

objects.name: Banking institutions
objects.description: Credit institutions whose business consists in receiving repayable funds from the public and granting credit. As the bank of banks, central banks are included in this scope.
Sector Banking institutions is a subsector of Finance

objects.name: Financial organizations
objects.description: Comprises for instance asset managers and investment firms, that are neither banks nor insurance companies.
Sector Financial organizations is a subsector of Finance

objects.name: Insurance services
objects.description: Companies, either insurance companies or mutual insurance companies, that provides insurance services to customers.
Sector Insurance services is a subsector of Finance

objects.name: Market infrastructures
objects.description: Encompasses all the systems necessary for the smooth process of market financing operations. Are included payment systems, clearing houses, central securities depositories, securities settlement systems and trade repositories.
Sector Market infrastructures is a subsector of Finance

objects.name: Diplomacy
objects.description: Public or private entities which are actors of or involved in international relations activities.

objects.name: Ministries of foreign affairs
objects.description: Governmental entities in charge of the diplomatic action of the State.
Sector Ministries of foreign affairs is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: Think tanks
objects.description: Research institutes and structures specialized in policy making and advocating on international relations subjects.
Sector Think tanks is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: International organizations
objects.description: International organizations made up primarily of sovereign states and involved in setting international agendas and policies.
Sector International organizations is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: Government and administrations
objects.description: Civilian government institutions and administrations of the executive and legislative branches. The diplomatic and judicial branches are not included.

objects.name: Central administration and government
objects.description: All central administrations and government bodies in charge of the executive power, except for the Ministries of Foreign Affairs, of Defense and of Justice.
Sector Central administration and government is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Local administrations
objects.description: Public administrations and government bodies managing a local territory under the global authority of a central government.
Sector Local administrations is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Legislative branch (parliamentary chambers)
objects.description: Legislative chambers of the state, in charge of voting the laws.
Sector Legislative branch (parliamentary chambers) is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Health
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in research, services and manufacturing activities related to public health.

objects.name: Healthcare services
objects.description: Hospitals and other direct medical practice activities.
Sector Healthcare services is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Pharmacy and drugs manufacturing
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in producing and selling medicinal products and drugs.
Sector Pharmacy and drugs manufacturing is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Healthcare research
objects.description: Entities involved in the scientific investigation of understanding how different factors affect people’s health and their access to healthcare.
Sector Healthcare research is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Hospitality
objects.description: Private entities offering to customers’ leisure activities and experiences.

objects.name: Lodging industry
objects.description: Entities offering short-term dwellings in exchange for money for people travelling or staying away from their home.
Sector Lodging industry is a subsector of Hospitality

objects.name: Food and drinks businesses
objects.description: Businesses preparing and serving food and drinks to customers in exchange for money.
Sector Food and drinks businesses is a subsector of Hospitality

objects.name: Travel and tourism industry
objects.description: Businesses operating in the field of travel for pleasure or business and in the field of attracting and entertaining tourists.
Sector Travel and tourism industry is a subsector of Hospitality

objects.name: Technologies
objects.description: Private entities related to the research, development, manufacturing and distribution of electronics, softwares, computers and products related to information technologies.

objects.name: High-tech
objects.description: Businesses involved in the conception and production of high technological equipment and goods in different fields such as biotechnologies, information technologies, nanotechnologies and robotics.
Sector High-tech is a subsector of Technologies

objects.name: Judicial power (justice)
objects.description: All judicial activities of the state and related private entities.

objects.name: Manufacturing
objects.description: Private entities transforming and selling goods, products and equipment which are not included in other activity sectors.

objects.name: Heavy industries
objects.description: Private entities working to transform raw materials into manufactured products (Chemicals, metal etc.).
Sector Heavy industries is a subsector of Manufacturing

objects.name: Construction
objects.description: Private entities engaged in preparation of land and construction, alteration and repair of building, structures and other real estate properties.
Sector Construction is a subsector of Manufacturing

objects.name: Retail (distribution)
objects.description: Distribution and sale of goods directly to the consumer.
Sector Retail (distribution) is a subsector of Manufacturing

objects.name: Telecommunications
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in the production, transport and dissemination of information and communication signals.

objects.name: Digital infrastructures
objects.description: All operators and entities in charge of operating and managing the digital infrastructures, including Internet Exchange Points, DNS providers and Top Level Domains Registrars.
Sector Digital infrastructures is a subsector of Telecommunications
Sector Hosting service providers is a subsector of Telecommunications
Sector Internet Service providers is a subsector of Telecommunications

objects.name: Medias and audiovisual
objects.description: Communication outlets used to deliver information by print, broadcast or Internet and people working in these outlets.
Sector Medias and audiovisual is a subsector of Telecommunications

objects.name: Consulting
objects.description: Private entities providing expert advice in a specific field to external entities.
Sector Legal consulting is a subsector of Consulting

objects.name: Information Technologies Consulting
objects.description: Includes Managed Services Providers (MSPs).
Sector Information Technologies Consulting is a subsector of Consulting
Sector Engineering consulting is a subsector of Consulting

objects.name: Mining
objects.description: Entities in charge of extracting minerals and other geological materials from the Earth.

objects.name: Research
objects.description: Private and public entities such as university research centers, labs, experimental centers etc. (except for defense, diplomacy and healthcare).

objects.name: Water distribution and supply
objects.description: All public and private entities involved in the collection, transport and distribution of water for consumption purposes.

objects.name: Civil society
objects.description: The general public and all non-governmental entities, or individuals independent of governments, which may be linked by interests or activities aiming at promoting the interests and the will of citizens.

objects.name: Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs)
objects.description: A legally constituted non-commercial organization created by natural or legal persons with no participation or representation of any government.
Sector Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs) is a subsector of Civil society

objects.name: Citizens
objects.description: The general population of a country.
Sector Citizens is a subsector of Civil society

objects.name: Political parties
objects.description: A recognized or non recognized political group or party taking part into the political life of a country, weither by being part of the majority or opposed to the ruling power
Sector Political parties is a subsector of Civil society

objects.name: Dissidents
objects.description: Individuals publicly disagreeing with and criticizing their government.
Sector Dissidents is a subsector of Civil society
